last_episode_to_air.name: The Dragon Boat Race
last_episode_to_air.overview: The Star Amigos enter a dragon boat race and enlist their friend, Eddie, to be their captain.

name: Nina's World
overview: Tag along with imaginative 6-year-old Nina on her neighborhood excursions with her best friends Carlos, Chelsea and Star – celebrating family, community, diversity and wonder.

episodes.name: Nina's Birthday
episodes.overview: Nina wants her sixth birthday to be the best birthday ever.

episodes.name: Nina's Big Adventure
episodes.overview: Nina is disappointed that she isn't going on a big adventure like TioJavier - but with a little imagination, she and Abuelita have their own adventure around the block.

episodes.name: Nina the Nurse
episodes.overview: Nina is so eager to help Abuelita recover from a cold that she neglects to ask Abuelita what she needs yo feel better.

episodes.name: Super Nina
episodes.overview: Nina and Carlos realize they don't need to be superheroes to be amazing - they can be helpful heroes and be just as awesome.

episodes.name: Nina Wants to Grow
episodes.overview: Nina wants to grow taller, but eventually she realizes there are positives for her current size.

episodes.name: Nina's Takes the Stage
episodes.overview: When Nina discovers a shadow puppet and a variety of costumes in the Everything Store, she and her friends decide to put on a play, but struggle on how to pick the right roles for each friend.

episodes.name: Nina Flies a Kite
episodes.overview: When Carlos accidentally breaks the kite he and Nina made for the Kite Festival, Nina is determined to make a new one with the help of her neighborhood friends.

episodes.name: Nina's First Sleepover
episodes.overview: Nina and Star try to be the perfect hosts when Chelsea stays at their house for a sleepover.

episodes.name: Nina from Space
episodes.overview: Nina sees her neighborhood in a different way when she and Chelsea pretend to be from another planet.

episodes.name: Nina Makes Music
episodes.overview: When Tio Javier is having trouble writing a song, Nina helps inspire him.

episodes.name: Nina Unplugged
episodes.overview: Nina sees an opportunity to bring family and friends together, when a blackout causes some concern on the block.

episodes.name: Nina the Great
episodes.overview: "Nina the Great" and "Chelsea the Magnificent" nearly let their competitive spirits get in the way of their magic show.

episodes.name: Nina the Artist
episodes.overview: Nina tries to paint a picture for a school art project but has such high expectations, she has trouble getting inspired on what to paint. After a frustrating attempt, Nina is disappointed with what she paints, but to her surprise, others seem to like it.

episodes.name: Nina and the Missing Myna Bird
episodes.overview: When Dr. Kapur's pet bird escapes, Nina and Star team up with their friends to rescue the music-loving Mynah Bird.

episodes.name: Nina Delivers
episodes.overview: Nina goes on an adventure to the post office, she becomes the'best delivery girl ever, discovering how packages are mailed to different parts of the world. Sending something 'from the heart' to family that is far away is the next best thing to being there.

episodes.name: Nina's Library Hop
episodes.overview: Determined to uncover the best home possible for her newly rescued frog-pal, Nina disrupts the peace and quiet at the library.

episodes.name: Nina and Papi Play Baseball
episodes.overview: When Nina wants to learn how to properly throw a baseball, she asks her dad, a former star high-school pitcher nicknamed El Bola De Fuego, to teach her. But Papi is upset his pitching aim is now WAY off so Nina decides to help her poor dad out.

episodes.name: Nina the Shadow Chaser
episodes.overview: While Skye is kid-sitting, Nina and Star watch a scary movie about a shadow monster and their imagination gets away from them.

episodes.name: Nina's Henna Hijinx
episodes.overview: When Dr. Kapur, a talented henna artist needs someone to practice on for niece's upcoming wedding, Nina eagerly volunteers. But little did Nina know that waiting for henna to dry is a lot easier said than done.

episodes.name: Nina's Everything Garden
episodes.overview: Nina learns to be open to new and different things, when she gets the chance to plant her own garden.

episodes.name: Nina's Family Museum
episodes.overview: In "Nina's Family Museum," when Nina, Mami and Abuelita miss out on a day at the museum, Nina decides to create her own mini-museum - of Flores family history!

episodes.name: Nina Dives In
episodes.overview: In "Nina Dives In," Nina really wants to learn how to swim, but she and Star are afraid of going into the new - and very big - community pool.

episodes.name: Nina Rides a Bike
episodes.overview: When Nina doesn't want to ride her bike after an accident, Abuelita Yolie, Carlos and Chelsea build her a 'bike school' to get her back on the bike.

episodes.name: Nina Takes the Cake
episodes.overview: Nina and Abuelita have an important job to do: deliver Mami's famous cakes to Eddie and Mrs. Goldstein. But when Nina tells a fib, cake chaos ensues!

episodes.name: Nina Dog Sits
episodes.overview: Carlos and Nico are going away for a while and have asked Nina to watch Max. However, Max has trouble sitting when Nina asks him to and makes a mess in her room - knocking down a chair, spilling glitter on the floor, and even ruining her painting of Star. Nina and Abuelita Yolie then give him a bath, where he seems to enjoy the hose.

episodes.name: Nina Gets on Track
episodes.overview: Abuelita is taking Nina to the library to see a railroad exhibit.

episodes.name: Nina's Show and Tell
episodes.overview: When she finds a flower growing in a sidewalk crack, Nina is eager to find a way to savor and share its beauty, and she does -- through photography.

episodes.name: Nina's Snow Day
episodes.overview: Nina gives homesick Chelsea a snow party - and learns what winter is like in another part of the world.

episodes.name: Nina Dances with Nico
episodes.overview: When Nina has difficulty learning a Mexican folk dance, she discovers through Nico that taking time to feel and enjoy the music is just as important as hearing the music.

episodes.name: Nina Bakes Bread
episodes.overview: In "Nina Bakes Bread," Nina and Chelsea are excited to do some baking in the Flores family bakery.

episodes.name: Nina's Special Dress
episodes.overview: In "Nina's Special Dress," Nina is so happy that Mami is making her a special dress for school picture day.

episodes.name: Nina Hunts for Treasure
episodes.overview: In "Nina Hunts for Treasure," Mr. Lin is taking Nina, Carlos and Chelsea out to the playground for a treasure hunt.

episodes.name: Nina Cleans Her Room
episodes.overview: Abuelita reminds Nina that she has to clean up her room before she can go outside to play with Chelsea. But, Nina gets distracted, finding many fascinating things to do in her room instead.

episodes.name: Nina's Brother for a Day
episodes.overview: When Nina's given a school project to report on a sibling, Carlos tells Nina they can share Nico.

episodes.name: Nina the Detective
episodes.overview: Detective Nina is on the case -when she discovers a peculiar object (a four-sided boomerang) and attempts to find its owner.

episodes.name: Nina's Old Oak Tree
episodes.overview: After weeks with no rain, Nina's favorite tree in the courtyard is drooping. She teams up with her friends to heal the tree and make it feel loved.

episodes.name: Nina Gets Packing
episodes.overview: It's Nina's first camping trip and she vows to be the most helpful camper ever by helping the family pack. But all her ideas and deeds are either overlooked or don't work out as the adults scramble to be on the road before dark.

episodes.name: Nina Camps It Up
episodes.overview: When Nina arrives at the campground she finds everything is very different from her home, and gets a little homesick. But after her family encourages her to try all the wonderful aspects of camping, like hiking, making new discoveries about nature, and cooking over an open fire, Nina soon comes to love living out in the woods.

episodes.name: Camp Nina
episodes.overview: Nina had such a great time camping that she now wants to share her experience with her friends, Chelsea and Carlos. But just when they pitch a homemade tent under the old oak, it starts to rain. Her outside camping fun is ruined - or is it.

episodes.name: Nina's Kickoff
episodes.overview: Nina is excited when Nico offers to give her, Chelsea and Carlos soccer lessons. But when Carlos feels Nico is getting all the attention and starts acting up, it ruins their practice. It's up to Nina to get the brothers back to being brotherly.

episodes.name: Nina's Game Day
episodes.overview: It's a special day as Nina and her friends Chelsea and Carlos compete in fun made-up games. But when Nina doesn't win any of the games, she becomes a bad sport and a sore loser.

episodes.name: Nina Learns Karate
episodes.overview: Nina tries her hand at karate and learns that some things require practice, stillness and focus.

episodes.name: To Mami, Love Nina
episodes.overview: It's Mother's Day and Nina is determined to give Mami a great present.

episodes.name: Nina's Lemonade Stand
episodes.overview: Like all little kids, Nina and Chelsea want new toys from the Everything Store...but to buy them, they need money!

episodes.name: Nina's Color Festival
episodes.overview: Nina's plan to create a colorful courtyard mural with Chelsea and Carlos goes awry, when her friends have an argument and decide not to take part.

episodes.name: Nina's Amazing Amigos
episodes.overview: When Nina, Chelsea and Carlos want to play on the playground at the park, they find themselves face-to-face with a bully.

episodes.name: Nina and the Yard Sale
episodes.overview: When the neighborhood has a yard sale, Nina is SHOCKED when she learns Papi is trying to get rid of some of her old toys. And now Nina is DETERMINED to keep them.

episodes.name: Nina and Papi's Best Day Ever
episodes.overview: When 'Father's Day' doesn't go quite like Nina had planned, Nina decides it's time for a do-over.

episodes.name: Nina the Babysitter
episodes.overview: When a baby comes to visit, Nina and Mami learn that it's not as easy as they thought it would be.

episodes.name: Nina's Thanksgiving
episodes.overview: When the oven breaks down in Chelsea's house, she worries that her Thanksgiving will be ruined, but Nina works to save the day.

episodes.name: Nina's Very Merry Gift
episodes.overview: Nina makes Christmas tree ornaments for her family and neighbors, but soon discovers that not everyone has a Christmas Tree, or even celebrates the same holiday - and yet they all embrace the season of giving and festive lights.

episodes.name: Nina Celebrates Chinese New Year
episodes.overview: Nina is excited when she and her family are invited to the Lins for Chinese New Year celebrations -- featuring a Lion Dance. Nina would love to have an outfit just like Skye has on. But the Lion Dance may be jeopardized when Nina, in her excitement, helps herself to red envelopes that, as it turns out, are meant for the performers.

episodes.name: Nina's Hanukkah Adventure
episodes.overview: A major snow storm is about to hit the city and it's the first night of Hanukkah. When Mrs. Goldstein discovers there is no oil of any kind available due to delayed shipments because of the rare storm, her plans to make her traditional Latkes and jelly donuts are in jeopardy. Enter Jennifer, her can-do, charismatic daughter, home for a visit. She leads Nina, Carlos, and Chelsea in a city-wide search to find vegetable oil for Mrs. Goldstein and olive oil for the Rabbi's Menorah.

episodes.name: Chelsea's Space Adventure
episodes.overview: When Chelsea discovers that she can't go to space camp this year, the Star Amigos will help her forget her disappointing news.

episodes.name: The Thanksgiving Sharing Box
episodes.overview: When efforts to fix the family float as well as get people to donate to the Thanksgiving Food Drive fail, Nina worries it's because she's a little kid.

episodes.name: Nina's Baker Boogie
episodes.overview: Nina really wants to win a dance contest with Papi, but her competitiveness gives Papi two left feet.

episodes.name: Letter to Santa
episodes.overview: Nina and friends must deliver a letter from her little brother to Santa Claus before Christmas.

episodes.name: Santi's Cranky Time
episodes.overview: Nina and friends try to figure out what Santi wants so he can nap before he throws a tantrum.

episodes.name: Max Gets Stinky
episodes.overview: Nina and her friends need to find a sweet-smelling solution to Max's skunky problem.

episodes.name: The Mysterious Food Truck
episodes.overview: Nina and her friends try to track down the food truck with the best Arepas in town.

episodes.name: The Lost Alpaca
episodes.overview: Nina and her friends must find a lost alpaca, which they accidentally let loose from the fair.

episodes.name: The Bear Trackers
episodes.overview: When Abuelita gives Nina a mysterious paper filled with random dots, she's told that it holds the key to finding a special bear in their neighborhood. Nina, Carlos, and Chelsea head out on a Bear hunt.

episodes.name: Number One Soccer Fan
episodes.overview: When Papi accidentally forgets to buy Mami's soccer game tickets, Nina and her friends save the day.

episodes.name: The Hand Me Down
episodes.overview: When Santi decides Lucy the Firefly flashlight is his favorite toy, Nina has a hard time giving up her old 'pal' to her little brother.

episodes.name: The Sneaky Spider
episodes.overview: Nina is determined to find and get rid of an ugly house spider that scares her in her bathroom, but she doesn't know enough about the bug to track it down, so Star takes Nina and the Amigos to the bug's world where they come to value the spider it for its contribution to keeping Nina's house safe.

episodes.name: Sky High Mystery
episodes.overview: When Chelsea takes a picture with an unidentified flying object in the background, she thinks she's discovered an alien spaceship. But has she?

episodes.name: Nina and Santi Celebrate Rakhi
episodes.overview: When Santi is a nuisance and Mr. Kapur explains a South Asian sibling appreciation tradition to her, Nina decides to try Rakhi with her little brother.

episodes.name: Star Goes Missing
episodes.overview: Nina's world turns upside down when she loses Star at the street fair.

episodes.name: Carlos Finds His Voice
episodes.overview: Right before the big Spring concert, Carlos gets a sore throat and must learn how to sing without using his voice.

episodes.name: Nina's Superhero Day
episodes.overview: Nina wants to win a costume contest. But when Papi loses his chance to meet his favorite comic book artist, she finds she'd rather help him meet his hero than win the contest.

episodes.name: The Best Thank You Gift Ever
episodes.overview: When Tio Javier does something nice for Nina and her friends, she wants to get him a present. As a result, the Star Amigos get "jobs" around the neighborhood so they can pay for it.

episodes.name: Nina's New Amigo
episodes.overview: A trip to the nursing home interrupts Nina's plans to play music with Tío Javier.

episodes.name: The Viva Lucha Libre Show
episodes.overview: After the Amigos watch Luchadors rehearse for a match, Carlos wants to create his own wrestling move. But he plays too rough and has to learn that there's plenty of fun in playing it safe.

episodes.name: Nina and the Dentist
episodes.overview: When Nina's scared about her upcoming dentist appointment, Nina enlists the Star Amigos' to help get rid of her fear, so she can be brave for her brother.

episodes.name: Nina's Nutty Adventure
episodes.overview: On the day of the bakery's big anniversary celebration, Nina wants to make the bakery, and everything else, safe for Aiden's nut allergy. But Nina takes her campaign too far and ends up making Aiden feel isolated instead.

episodes.name: Nina's Marionette Show
episodes.overview: Nina wants to give Abuelita Yolie a special gift: a Mexican marionette show like the one she saw in her youth.

episodes.name: The New Nina
episodes.overview: When Nina's favorite cousin Natalia visits from Mexico, Nina feels left out because everyone seems to like Natalia more than her.

episodes.name: Nina Misses Mami and Papi
episodes.overview: When Nina's parents take a weekend trip without the kids for the first time ever, Nina can't get over missing them.

episodes.name: Chelsea's Slam Dunk
episodes.overview: As the Star Amigos prepare to play Tío Javier in a 3-on-1 basketball rematch, Chelsea hurts her ankle and has a hard time watching from the sidelines.

episodes.name: Chelsea's Family Day
episodes.overview: Chelsea learns that there is no such thing as a 'regular' family. There are all kinds of different, equally valid, family models in the world. She can still have fun as a family even if her parents are apart.

episodes.name: Nina and Abuelita's Special Day
episodes.overview: Nina tries to have Abuelita all to herself, but realizes that sometimes sharing those you love is a lot more fun.

episodes.name: Nina Finds a Kitten
episodes.overview: Nina finds a lost kitten and hopes to keep it for herself.

episodes.name: Nina's Big Race
episodes.overview: After Dr. Kapur tells Nina of a charity run to help benefit the local animal shelter, she's very excited, especially when Abuelita and Mami decide to join her. But this "Pet-A-Thon" proves to be a lot tougher than Nina expected.

episodes.name: The Great Pita Fajita
episodes.overview: Nina and Hameed team up for their school's Food Fair by making the world's first Pita Fajita, but soliciting too much input from their friends makes them question whether it's as tasty as they originally thought.

episodes.name: Happy Anniversary Mami and Papi
episodes.overview: When Mami and Papi are too busy to organize an anniversary dinner, Nina and the Star Amigos take it upon themselves to cook a special meal for them.

episodes.name: Max Wants to Play
episodes.overview: When Max the Dog gets hurt, Carlos learns that accidents happen though we do everything we can to avoid them. When an accident happens, you take care of it and then get back to normal as soon as possible.

episodes.name: The New Clubhouse
episodes.overview: When a storm wrecks their Clubhouse, Nina and friends don't believe that they can be the Star Amigos without it. But as they search for a new clubhouse, they find that they're still super Star Amigo helpers.

episodes.name: Nina's Seaside Rescue
episodes.overview: Nina learns that sometimes rivals need to put aside their differences and work together for the common good.

episodes.name: Nina Live!
episodes.overview: Nina gets the chance to play a song with a famous salsa singer, but first she must get over her fear of playing a new instrument.

episodes.name: Nina in Charge
episodes.overview: Nina volunteers to be in charge of the kids at a neighborhood BBQ. But when Abuelita offers a piñata for the event, and the kids would rather play with it than do the long list of activities Nina has planned, she has to learn to adjust.

episodes.name: Carlos' Winning Shirt
episodes.overview: Carlos thinks he can only win the big soccer game if he wears his brother Nico's "winning" t-shirt.

episodes.name: The Best Ending Ever
episodes.overview: When pages from Nina's picture book go missing, the Star Amigos have to come up with a new ending so that Santi will go to sleep.

episodes.name: Nina the Nature Guide
episodes.overview: The Star Amigos head into the woods for a hiking trip and things don't go as planned.

episodes.name: Nina's Bad Hair Day
episodes.overview: The Star Amigos must help Nina fix her hair for family photo day.

episodes.name: Chelsea's History Mystery
episodes.overview: Chelsea has trouble finding the perfect personal artifact to contribute to a neighborhood history exhibit.

episodes.name: Nina and Her Shadow
episodes.overview: The Star Amigos plan to make a music video for cousin Natalia's birthday.

episodes.name: Carlos Rocks Ballet
episodes.overview: Nina and Chelsea ask Carlos to join their ballet trio.

episodes.name: Nina in the Middle
episodes.overview: Nina plans to put on a play for Santi's playgroup.

episodes.name: Nina's Top Secret Party
episodes.overview: Nina overhears something, leading her to believe that Chelsea is moving away.

episodes.name: Don Pablo Goes to the Game
episodes.overview: After finding it very difficult to get to Bear Stadium, Nina decides it's time to make some changes around town.

episodes.name: The Star Amigos' Art Show
episodes.overview: The Star Amigos put on an art show, but Nina accidentally ruins Carlos' sculpture.

episodes.name: Wish You Were Here
episodes.overview: When Nina's friends and neighbors go away on vacation, she tries to have a "stay-cation" at home.

episodes.name: Do Everything Day!
episodes.overview: With summer almost over, the Star Amigos rush to complete their summer to-do list.

episodes.name: The Dragon Boat Race
episodes.overview: The Star Amigos enter a dragon boat race and enlist their friend, Eddie, to be their captain.
